SIMPLE: foreshow
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foreshow
<hw>Fore*show"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>foresce⟦aacute⟧wian</ets> to foresee, provide; <ets>fore +
sce⟦aacute⟧wian</ets> to see. See <er>Show</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety>
<def>To show or exhibit beforehand; to give foreknowledge of; to
prognosticate; to foretell.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Your looks <qex>foreshow</qex>⟦br⟧
You have a gentle heart.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Next, like Aurora, Spenser rose,⟦br⟧
Whose purple blush the day <qex>foreshows</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreshower</ent>⟦br⟧
